This time of year I usually struggle the most with anxiety and sleep. Last year I posted about it and connected with many of you deeply and that was rad. I'm not sure if it's getting ready for the winter and gearing up for pushing myself and performing at the top of my game, or if it's simply the season. In Ayurveda this is the typical season to struggle with anxiety and overwhelm- and personally those affect my sleep. .

This year, because of lifestyle changes I‚Äôve made to remove stress and be more mindful, my anxiety has been better but still present. I‚Äôm learning to sit with it. In my morning meditations I make friends with it and don‚Äôt make it try to go away. I‚Äôm like, what‚Äôs up dude! I was waiting for you to join the party! Let‚Äôs have some tea and hang out! Then it usually gets better. In any case, I was sleeping horribly for the past month and a half... waking up at 3-3:30 and being tired but wired. I was trying lots of different stuff and balancing Ayurvedically and that helped a lot but I was still sleeping poorly. .
I was thinking, maybe I should try some supplement or something to calm my nervous system down a bit and I had kind of a hilarious moment where I realize I am a sponsored athlete and now CBD is in the mix. The following is both a sponsored athlete endorsement (don‚Äôt choke while you gag yourself!) and a legit human endorsement, as I hope you guys know I try not to blow smoke up your bungjulio haha and it‚Äôs why I pick and choose my brands. Long story short I am on again off again with supplements but I travel with my go-tos and had my @cbdistillery_ stuff with me but hadn‚Äôt been taking it. When I‚Äôm operating well, the ingestible stuff isnt as immediately noticeable as the salve, so I figured this was the perfect opportunity to give some of their products a good test. .
Guys. I‚Äôm not saying it will work for everyone. Or every case. All I know is after like 7 weeks of waking up EVERY night at 3 am,2 days after I started taking their tincture, I slept well the whole night and didn‚Äôt wake up. Interesting. Next post with these guys will about dosages esp for entry level peeps.

If you‚Äôve been wondering what I‚Äôve been doing in Hawaii besides sitting in silence for 10 days, I‚Äôm counterbalancing it with perfecting my spoof acting skills. I‚Äôll be accepting applications for advertisement jobs anytime now... oh wait... that‚Äôs my job.... ü§∑üèº‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è #icanseemychesthairsfromhere  @smithoptics #smithoptics #screwthisbeachstuffimgoinghome#pursueyourthrill üé• @thrillauer

Got to watch the Jaws comp yesterday. Holy chicken nuggets every time it's mindblowing. From the intensity of big days filming in the mountains, I was both envious of the athletes and relieved I got to be a mellow spectator. The way those days require your full presence and attention, make you feel alive and in tune with the environment around you. I was also not envious at all- those days are scary and challenging and being in a safe environment watching the show was easy, comfortable, and pleasurable. I value each side of the experience equally. The crazy thing about surfing and the ocean is the waves don't stop after you wipe out. Or like in the mountains, unless you're mid-line, you can usually take a minute and assess- with surfing you have to always be making the decisions quickly. Huge congrats to @paigealms. Queen!!! So impressive. So proud of you!!! üì∑ @thrillauer

Today would‚Äôve been Shane McConkey‚Äôs 50th birthday.  It‚Äôs crazy to think he left us more than a decade ago, but the brightness with which his flame still burns is a testament to the kind of guy he was. 
The late Andreas Fransson once told me that since there is no clear answer about what happens to a person after they die, we are free to create the reality we want. 
A couple of days ago there was a big raven waiting for us on a post at the top of the skin track in the Whistler backcountry. After watching it for a bit, I got my phone out to take a couple of shots. It turned its head a few times to make sure I got the portrait, then launched into an arc in a ‚Äòcheck me out!‚Äô kind of way.  Such a McConkey thing to do. 
Thanks Shane!
